.SH NAME
.PP
SecureSdb \- Create a SecureSdb object.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
\f[B]\f[I]new SecureSdb( [hostname], [svcname] )\f[]\f[]
.PP
\f[B]\f[I]var securesdb = new SecureSdb( [hostname], [svcname], [username],
[password] )\f[]\f[]
.SH CATEGORY
.PP
SecureSdb
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Create a SecureSdb object.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[]
.RE
.RS
.IP "1." 3
SecureSdb is subclass of Sdb and SecureSdb object uses SSL connection.
.RE
.RS
.IP "2." 3
The method and syntax of the SecureSdb object and the Sdb object are the same.
.RE
