.SH RETURN VALUE
.PP
On success, return a SecureSdb.
.PP
On error, exception will be thrown.
.SH ERRORS
.PP
When exception happen, use getLastError() to get the error code and use
getLastErrMsg() to get error message.
For more detial, please reference to Troubleshooting.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP "1." 3
Create a SecureSdb object.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ var\ securesdb\ =\ new\ SecureSdb(\ "192.168.20.71",\ 11790\ )
\f[]
.fi
.RE
.IP "2." 3
Create a SecureSdb object with a username and password.
.nf
\f[C]
>\ var\ securesdb\ =\ new\ SecureSdb("sdbserver1",11810,"sdbadmin","123")
\f[]
.fi
.RE
